@description: Acre-foot is volume unit, symbol: [ac ft]. Definition of 1 acre-foot ≡ 1 ac × ft ≡ 43560 cu ft. The acre-foot is a unit of volume commonly used in US in reference to large-scale water resources ≡ 1 acre (international) × ft cuboid ≡ 1233.48183754752 m³.

Acre-inch is volume unit, symbol: [ac in]. Definition of 1 acre-inch ≡ 1 ac × in. Acre-inch is unit of volume commonly used as smaller unit of acre-foot, reference to large-scale water resources ≡ 102.79015312896 m³.
Barrel (imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [bl (imp)]. Definition of 1 barrel (imperial) ≡ 36 gal (imp). ≡ 36×0.00454609 m³ ≡ 0.16365924 m³.
"<b>Barrel (petroleum)
"<b>Barrel (petroleum)
Barrel (US dry) is volume unit, symbol: [bl (US)]. Definition of 1 barrel (US dry) ≡ 105 qt (US) ≡ 105/32 bu (US lvl). ≡ 105 / 32 × (2150.42 × 0.0254 × 0.0254 × 0.0254) ≡ 0.115628198985075 m³.
Barrel (US fluid) is volume unit, symbol: [fl bl (US)]. Definition of 1 barrel (US fluid) ≡ 31 1⁄2 gal (US). ≡ 31.5×0.003785411784 ≡ 0.119240471196 m³.
Board-foot is volume unit, symbol: [fbm]. Definition of 1 board-foot ≡ 144 cu in. The board-foot is volume unit of lumber in the United States and Canada..
Bucket (imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [bkt]. Definition of 1 bucket (imperial) ≡ 4 gal (imp). ≡ 4×0.00454609 ≡ 0.01818436 m³.

Bushel (imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [bu (imp)]. Definition of 1 bushel (imperial) ≡ 8 gal (imp). An imperial bushel was unit of weight or mass based upon an earlier measure of dry capacity. ≡ 0.03636872 m³.
Bushel (US dry heaped) is volume unit, symbol: [bu (US)]. Definition of 1 bushel (US dry heaped) ≡ 1 1⁄4 bu (US lvl). ≡ 1.25 × (2150.42×0.0254³) ≡ 0.0440488377086 m³.
Bushel (US dry level) is volume unit, symbol: [bu (US lvl)]. Definition of 1 bushel (US dry level) ≡ 2150.42 cu in. ≡ 2150.42 × 0.0254³ ≡ 0.03523907016688 m³.
Butt, pipe is volume unit. Definition of 1 butt, pipe ≡ 126 gal (wine). The US butt (or pipe) was a measure of liquid volume equalling two hogsheads or 126 US gallons ≡ 0.476961884784 m³.
Centilitre is metric volume unit, symbol: [cL]. Definition of 1 centilitre ≡ 0.01 L. One centilitre is volume equivalent to hundreds of Litre (L/100).
Coomb is volume unit. Definition of 1 coomb ≡ 4 bu (imp). A coomb is a measure of volume. In 13th century it was defined as 4 imperial bushels ≡ 0.14547488 m³.
Cord (firewood) is volume unit. Definition of 1 cord (firewood) ≡ 8 ft × 4 ft × 4 ft. ≡ 8 × 4 × 4 × 0.3048³ ≡ 3.624556363776 m³.
Cord-foot is volume unit. Definition of 1 cord-foot ≡ 16 cu ft. ≡ 16 × 0.3048³≡ 0.453069545472 m³.

Cubic centimetre is metric volume unit, symbol: [cm³]. Definition of 1 cubic centimetre ≡ 1 cm × cm × cm. One cubic centimetre is volume equivalent to cube with base of 1 cm. In 1 litre there are 1000 cubic centimetres..
Cubic decimetre is metric volume unit, symbol: [dm³]. Definition of 1 cubic decimetre ≡ 1 dm × dm × dm. One cubic decimetre is volume equivalent to one litre. .
Cubic dekametre is metric volume unit, symbol: [dam³]. Definition of 1 cubic dekametre ≡ 1 dam × dam × dam. Equivalent to volume of 10 m × 10 m × 10 m cube ≡ thousands of cubic metre..
Cubic fathom is volume unit, symbol: [cu fm]. Definition of 1 cubic fathom ≡ 1 fm × fm × fm. ≡ 1.8288³ ≡ 6.116438863872 m³.
Cubic foot is volume unit, symbol: [cu ft]. Definition of 1 cubic foot ≡ 1 ft × ft × ft. ≡ 0.3048³ ≡ 0.028316846592 m³.
Cubic hectometre is metric volume unit, symbol: [hm³]. Definition of 1 cubic hectometre ≡ 1 hm × hm × hm. One million of cubic metres. For example lake Balaton (in Hungary) has volume of 1900 hm³.
Cubic inch is volume unit, symbol: [cu in]. Definition of 1 cubic inch ≡ 1 in × in × in. ≡ 0.0254³ ≡ 16.387064×10^-6 m³.

Cubic kilometre is metric volume unit, symbol: [km³]. Definition of 1 cubic kilometre ≡ 1 km × km × km. One cubic kilometre is very large volume. For example Caspian Sea has water volume of 78,200 km³.
Cubic metre is volume unit, symbol: [m³]. Definition of 1 cubic metre ≡ 1 m × m × m. ≡ SI unit for volume is 1 m³ ≡ 1m × 1m ×1m size cube..
Cubic micrometre is metric volume unit, symbol: [µm³]. Definition of 1 cubic micrometre ≡ 1 µm × µm × µm. It is a very small volume unit. One millionth of microlitre..
Cubic mile is volume unit, symbol: [cu mi]. Definition of 1 cubic mile ≡ 1 mi × mi × mi. ≡ 1609.344³ ≡ 4168181825.440579584 m³.
Cubic millimetre is metric volume unit, symbol: [mm³]. Definition of 1 cubic millimetre ≡ 1 mm × mm × mm. Cube with size 1 mm × mm × mm has volume of 1 mm³.
Cubic nanometre is metric volume unit, symbol: [nm³]. Definition of 1 cubic nanometre ≡ 1 nm × nm × nm. Very small volume equivalent to one nanometre-based cubic volume..
Cubic yard is volume unit, symbol: [cu yd]. Definition of 1 cubic yard ≡ 27 cu ft. ≡ 0.9144³ ≡ 0.764554857984 m³ (1 yard ≡ 0.9144 m).
Cup (breakfast) is volume unit. Definition of 1 cup (breakfast) ≡ 10 fl oz (imp). A unit of liquid volume, used in food recipes in Britain ≡ 284.130625×10^-6 m³.
Cup (Canadian) is volume unit, symbol: [c (CA)]. Definition of 1 cup (Canadian) ≡ 8 fl oz (imp). ≡ 8 × 0.0000284130625 ≡ 227.3045×10^-6 m³.
Cup (metric) is volume unit, symbol: [c]. Definition of 1 cup (metric) ≡ 250.0×10^-6 m³. Metric cup ≡ 250 mL ≡ 250.0×10^-6 m³.

Cup (US customary) is volume unit, symbol: [c (US)]. Definition of 1 cup (US customary) ≡ 8 US fl oz ≡ 1⁄16 gal (US). United States customary cup is defined as half a U.S. pint or 1/16 of US gallon ≡ 236.5882365×10^-6 m³.

Cup (US food nutrition labeling) is volume unit, symbol: [c (US)]. Definition of 1 cup (US food nutrition labeling) ≡ 240 mL. The cup currently used in the United States for nutrition labelling is defined in United States law as 240 ml ≡ 2.4×10^-4 m³.
Dash (imperial) is volume unit. Definition of 1 dash (imperial) ≡ 1⁄384 gi (imp) ≡ 1⁄2 pinch (imp). ≡ 5 × 0.0000284130625 / 384 ≡ 369.96175130208(3)×10^-9 m³.
Dash (US) is volume unit. Definition of 1 dash (US) ≡ 1⁄96 US fl oz ≡ 1⁄2 US pinch. ≡ 0.0000295735295625 / 96 ≡ 308.057599609375×10^-9 m³.
Decilitre is metric volume unit, symbol: [dL]. Definition of 1 decilitre ≡ 0.1 L. Decilitre is volume equivalent to one tenth of a liter (L/10).
Dekalitre is metric volume unit, symbol: [daL]. Definition of 1 dekalitre ≡ 10 L. Dekalitre is equivalent to volume of ten litres.

Dessertspoon (imperial) is volume unit. Definition of 1 dessertspoon (imperial) ≡ 1⁄12 gi (imp). A dessertspoon unit of volume based on a spoon designed specifically for eating dessert. ≡ 11.8387760416×10^-6 m³.
Drop (imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [gtt (imp)]. Definition of 1 drop (imperial) ≡ 1⁄288 fl oz (imp). Most common definition for imperial drop is fl oz (imp)/288 ≡ 98.6564670138×10^-9 m³.
Drop (medical) is volume unit, symbol: [gtt (med.)]. Definition of 1 drop (medical) ≡ 1⁄12 ml. Medical drop is defined ad 1 mL / 12 ≡ 83.33(3)×10^-9 m³.
Drop (metric) is volume unit, symbol: [gtt (metric)]. Definition of 1 drop (metric) ≡ 1⁄20 mL. Metric drop: 1 mL/20 ≡ 50.0×10^-9 m³.
Drop (US) is volume unit, symbol: [gtt (US)]. Definition of 1 drop (US) ≡ 1⁄360 US fl oz. Most common definition for US drop is US fl oz/30 ≡ 82.14869322916×10^-9 m³.
Fifth is volume unit. Definition of 1 fifth ≡ 1⁄5 US gal. Fifth part of US gallon ≡ 0.003785411784 / 5 ≡ 757.0823568×10^-6 m³.
Firkin is volume unit. Definition of 1 firkin ≡ 9 gal (imp). Firkin is equal to nine imperial gallon ≡ 9×0.00454609 ≡ 0.04091481 m³.
Fluid drachm (imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [fl dr]. Definition of 1 fluid drachm (imperial) ≡ 1⁄8 fl oz (imp). Drachm is British spelling for dram: fl oz (imperial) / 8 ≡ 3.5516328125×10^-6 m³.
Fluid dram (US) is volume unit, symbol: [fl dr]. Definition of 1 fluid dram (US) ≡ 1⁄8 US fl oz. Fluid dram (or Drachm in UK spelling) ≡ US fl oz / 8 ≡ 3.6966911953125×10^-6 m³.

Fluid scruple (imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [fl s]. Definition of 1 fluid scruple (imperial) ≡ 1⁄24 fl oz (imp). The scruple is a small unit in the apothecaries system, derived from the old Roman scrupulum unit, equal to: fl oz (imp) / 24 ≡ 1.18387760416×10^-6 m³.

Gallon (beer) is volume unit, symbol: [beer gal]. Definition of 1 gallon (beer) ≡ 282 cu in. The gallon originated as the base of systems for measuring wine, and beer in England ≡ 282 cubic inch ≡ 4.621152048×10^-3 m³.
Gallon (imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [gal (imp)]. Definition of 1 gallon (imperial) ≡ 4.54609 L. Since 1985 one imperial gallon is exactly defnied as ≡ 4.54609×10^-3 m³.
Gallon (US dry) is volume unit, symbol: [gal (US dry)]. Definition of 1 gallon (US dry) ≡ 1⁄8 bu (US lvl). Dry US gallon is a rarely used and unofficial unit of measure ≡ 4.40488377086×10^-3 m³.

column12: Noggin ≡ 5 fl oz (imp). The imperial gill or teacup is a unit of measurement for volume equal to a quarter of a imperial pint ≡ 142.0653125×10^-6 m³."

column12: Noggin ≡ 5 fl oz (imp). The imperial gill or teacup is a unit of measurement for volume equal to a quarter of a imperial pint ≡ 142.0653125×10^-6 m³."

@description: Gill (US) is volume unit, symbol: [gi (US)]. Definition of 1 gill (US) ≡ 4 US fl oz. The US gill is a unit of measurement for volume equal to a quarter of a US pint ≡ 118.29411825×10^-6 m³.
Hectolitre is metric volume unit, symbol: [hL]. Definition of 1 hectolitre ≡ 100 L. Hectolitre is equivalent to volume of hundred litres.
Hogshead (imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [hhd (imp)]. Definition of 1 hogshead (imperial) ≡ 2 bl (imp). Hogshead is a large cask of liquid. Imperial hogshead is equal to 0.32731848 m³.
Hogshead (US) is volume unit, symbol: [hhd (US)]. Definition of 1 hogshead (US) ≡ 2 fl bl (US). US hogshead is a large cask of liquid, equal to ≡ 0.238480942392 m³.

Jigger (bartending) is volume unit. Definition of 1 jigger (bartending) ≡ 1 1⁄2 US fl oz. A jigger or measure is a bartending tool used to measure liquor, which is typically then poured into a cocktail shaker..
Kilderkin is volume unit. Definition of 1 kilderkin ≡ 18 gal (imp). The kilderkin (from the Dutch for small cask) is equal to half a barrel or two firkins or 18 imperial gallons ≡ 0.08182962 m³.
Lambda is volume unit, symbol: [λ]. Definition of 1 lambda ≡ 1 mm³. Lambda is a legit metric unit of volume equal to ≡ 1×10^-9 m³.

Last is volume unit. Definition of 1 last ≡ 80 bu (imp). The last was a large English unit of volume. It referred to standardized amounts of ships lading and varied by commodity and over time ≡ 2.9094976 m³.
Litre is volume unit, symbol: [L]. Definition of 1 litre ≡ 1 dm³. Litre (or Liter spelling in American English) is very popular unit of volume equal to 10 cm × 10 cm × 10 cm cube ≡ 0.001 m³.
Load is volume unit. Definition of 1 load ≡ 50 cu ft. Load volume unit is equal to 50 cubic feet ≡ 50 × 0.3048³ ≡ 1.4158423296 m³.
Microlitre is metric volume unit, symbol: [µL]. Definition of 1 microlitre ≡ 10^-6 L. One microlitre volume is equivalent to one millionth of Litre ≡ 1 cubic millimetre.
Millilitre is metric volume unit, symbol: [mL]. Definition of 1 millilitre ≡ 0.001 L. One millilitre is volume equivalent to one cubic centimetre.

Minim (imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [min]. Definition of 1 minim (imperial) ≡ 1⁄480 fl oz (imp) ≡ 1/60 fl dr (imp). Imperial minim is volume unit equal to 1/480 part of imperial ounce ≡ 59.1938802083×10^-9 m³.

@definition: 1⁄480 US fl oz = 1⁄60 US fl dr
@description: Minim (US) is volume unit, symbol: [min]. Definition of 1 minim (US) ≡ 1⁄480 US fl oz ≡ 1⁄60 US fl dr. US minim is volume unit equal to 1/480 part of US fluid ounce≡ 61.611519921875×10^-9 m³.

Ounce (fluid imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [fl oz (imp)]. Definition of 1 ounce (fluid imperial) ≡ 1⁄160 gal (imp). Imperial fluid ounce is unit of volume (or capacity) equal to 1/160 of imperial gallon ≡ 28.4130625×10^-6 m³.

Ounce (fluid US customary) is volume unit, symbol: [US fl oz]. Definition of 1 ounce (fluid US customary) ≡ 1⁄128 gal (US). US fluid ounce is unit of volume (or capacity) equal to 1/128 of US fluid gallon ≡ 29.5735295625×10^-6 m³.
Ounce (fluid US food nutrition labeling) is volume unit, symbol: [US fl oz]. Definition of 1 ounce (fluid US food nutrition labeling) ≡ 30 mL. By definition exactly 30 mL ≡ 3×10^-5 m³.

Peck (imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [pk]. Definition of 1 peck (imperial) ≡ 2 gal (imp). A peck is an imperial (and US customary) unit of dry volume equivalent to 2 imperial gallons ≡ 9.09218×10^-3 m³.

Peck (US dry) is volume unit, symbol: [pk]. Definition of 1 peck (US dry) ≡ 1⁄4 US lvl bu. US peck is an US customary (and imperial) unit of dry volume equivalent to 2 US dry gallons ≡ 8.80976754172×10^-3 m³.
Perch is volume unit, symbol: [per]. Definition of 1 perch ≡ 16 1⁄2 ft × 1 1⁄2 ft × ft. Perch is a traditional unit of volume for stone and other masonry 24.75 cu ft ≡ 0.700841953152 m³.
Picolitre is metric volume unit, symbol: [pL]. Definition of 1 picolitre ≡ 10^-9 L. One picolitre is very small unit. 1 mL contains million picolitres..

Pinch (imperial) is volume unit. Definition of 1 pinch (imperial) ≡ 1⁄192 gi (imp) ≡ 1/16 tsp (imp). Imperial pinch is a kitchen volume unit used to dose salt, sugar, spice ≡ 739.92350260416×10^-9 m³.
Pinch (US) is volume unit. Definition of 1 pinch (US) ≡ 1⁄48 US fl oz ≡ 1/16 US tsp. US pinch is kitchen US (dry) Volume Unit ≡ 616.11519921875×10^-9 m³.
Pint (imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [pt (imp)]. Definition of 1 pint (imperial) ≡ 1⁄8 gal (imp). Imperial pint is unit of volume equal to one-eighth of an imperial gallon ≡ 568.26125×10^-6 m³.

Pint (US dry) is volume unit, symbol: [pt (US dry)]. Definition of 1 pint (US dry) ≡ 1⁄64 bu (US lvl) ≡ 1⁄8 gal (US dry). US dry pint is unit of volume equal to one-eighth of an US dry gallon ≡ 550.6104713575×10^-6 m³.
Pint (US fluid) is volume unit, symbol: [pt (US fl)]. Definition of 1 pint (US fluid) ≡ 1⁄8 gal (US). US fluid pint is unit of volume equal to one-eighth of an US liquid gallon≡ 473.176473×10^-6 m³.
Pony is volume unit. Definition of 1 pony ≡ 3⁄4 US fl oz. According to Encyclopædia Britannica Almanac 2009, a pony is 0.75 fluid ounces of liquor ≡ 22.180147171875×10^-6 m³.

@description: Quart (imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [qt (imp)]. Definition of 1 quart (imperial) ≡ 1⁄4 gal (imp). Quart of an imperial gallon ≡ 1.1365225×10^-3 m³.
Quart (US dry) is volume unit, symbol: [qt (US)]. Definition of 1 quart (US dry) ≡ 1⁄32 bu (US lvl) ≡ 1⁄4 gal (US dry). Quart of an US dry gallon ≡ 1.101220942715×10^-3 m³.
Quart (US fluid) is volume unit, symbol: [qt (US)]. Definition of 1 quart (US fluid) ≡ 1⁄4 gal (US fl). Quart of an US fluid gallon ≡ 946.352946×10^-6 m³.

column10: pail is volume unit. Definition of 1 quarter
column11: pail ≡ 8 bu (imp). Equivalent to 8 imperial bushels: 8 × 0.03636872 ≡ 0.29094976 m³."

@description: "Register ton is volume unit. Definition of 1 register ton ≡ 100 cu ft. Gross register tonnage a ship's total internal volume expressed in \"register tons\", each of which is equal to 100 cubic feet ≡ 2.8316846592 m³."

@description: Sack (US) is volume unit. Definition of 1 sack (US) ≡ 3 bu (US lvl). Sack is dry unit equivalent to 3 US level bushels ≡ 0.10571721050064 m³.
Seam is volume unit. Definition of 1 seam ≡ 8 bu (imperial). A Seam is an obsolete unit of volume in the UK ≡ 0.29094976 m³.

Shot (US) is volume unit. Definition of 1 shot (US) usually 1.5 US fl oz. Shot is a traditional unit of liquid volume. In the U.S. a shot is usually the same as a jigger 1.5 US fl oz ≡ 44.4 ml (but some bartenders use shot glasses of other sizes such as 1.25 US fl oz).
Strike (imperial) is volume unit. Definition of 1 strike (imperial) ≡ 2 bu (imp). Imperial strike unit of volume equivalent to two imperial bushels ≡ 0.07273744 m³.
Strike (US) is volume unit. Definition of 1 strike (US) ≡ 2 bu (US lvl). US strike is unit of volume equivalent to two US level bushels ≡ 0.07047814033376 m³.
Tablespoon (Australian metric) is volume unit. Definition of 1 tablespoon (Australian metric) ≡ 20 ml. Defined as exactly 20 mL ≡ 20.0×10^-6 m³.
Tablespoon (Canadian) is volume unit, symbol: [tbsp]. Definition of 1 tablespoon (Canadian) ≡ 1⁄2 fl oz (imp). ≡ 28.4130625 mL /2 ≡ 14.20653125×10^-6 m³.

Tablespoon (imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [tbsp (imp)]. Definition of 1 tablespoon (imperial) ≡ 5⁄8 fl oz (imp). Imperial tablespoon is a unit of volume, especially widely used in cooking recipes and pharmaceutic prescriptions, equivalent with 5/8 imperial fluid ounce ≡ 17.7581640625×10^-6 m³.
Tablespoon (metric) is volume unit, symbol: [tbsp (metric)]. Definition of 1 tablespoon (metric) ≡ 15 ml. Metric tablespoon is exactly 15 mL ≡ 15.0×10^-6 m³.

Tablespoon (US customary) is volume unit, symbol: [tbsp (US)]. Definition of 1 tablespoon (US customary) ≡ 1⁄2 US fl oz. The traditional US interpretation of the tablespoon as a unit of volume is 3 teaspoons or half US fluid ounce≡ 14.78676478125×10^-6 m³.

Tablespoon (US food nutrition labeling) is volume unit, symbol: [tbsp]. Definition of 1 tablespoon (US food nutrition labeling) ≡ 15 mL. Tablespoon for US food nutrition labeling is same as metric tablespoon, 15 mL ≡ 1.5×10^-5 m³.

Teaspoon (Canadian) is volume unit, symbol: [tsp]. Definition of 1 teaspoon (Canadian) ≡ 1⁄6 fl oz (imp). Canadian teaspoon is volume unit equivalent with one sixth of imperial fluid ounce ≡ 4.73551041(6)×10^-6 m³.

Teaspoon (imperial) is volume unit, symbol: [tsp (imp)]. Definition of 1 teaspoon (imperial) ≡ 1⁄24 gi (imp). Imperial teaspoon is volume unit (widely used in cooking recipes) equivalent with 1/24 of imperial gill ≡ 5.91938802083×10^-6 m³.
Teaspoon (metric) is volume unit, symbol: [tsp (metric)]. Definition of 1 teaspoon (metric) ≡ 5 ml. Metric teaspoon is exactly 5 mL ≡ 5.0×10^-6 m³.

Teaspoon (US customary) is volume unit, symbol: [tsp (US)]. Definition of 1 teaspoon (US customary) ≡ 1⁄6 US fl oz. US teaspoon is volume unit with capacity of one sixth of US fluid ounce ≡ 4.92892159375×10^-6 m³.

Teaspoon (US food nutrition labeling) is volume unit, symbol: [tsp]. Definition of 1 teaspoon (US food nutrition labeling) ≡ 5 mL. Teaspoon (US food nutrition labeling) have same capacity as metric teaspoon ≡ 5 mL ≡ 5×10^-6 m³.
Timber foot is volume unit. Definition of 1 timber foot ≡ 1 cu ft. Timperfoot is other name for cubic foot, cube with size of 1 ft × ft × ft ≡ 0.028316846592 m³.

Ton (displacement) is volume unit, symbol: [DT]. Definition of 1 ton (displacement) ≡ 35 cu ft. The displacement, essentially the weight, of a ship is traditionally expressed in long tons. To simplify measurement it is determined by measuring the volume, rather than weight ≡ 35 × 0.3048³ ≡ 0.99108963072 m³.
Ton (freight) is volume unit. Definition of 1 ton (freight) ≡ 40 cu ft. The freight ton represents the volume of a truck, train or other freight carrier ≡ 40 × 0.3048³ ≡ 1.13267386368 m³.

Ton (water) is volume unit. Definition of 1 ton (water) ≡ 28 bu (imp). The water ton is used chiefly in Great Britain, in statistics dealing with petroleum products, and is defined as 224 imperial gallons ≡ 1.01832416 m³.
Tun is volume unit. Definition of 1 tun ≡ 252 gal (wine). One tun is volume equivalent to 252 gallons (wine) ≡ 0.953923769568 m³.
Wey (US) is volume unit. Definition of 1 wey (US) ≡ 40 bu (US lvl). As a measure of volume for dry commodities, it denoted roughly 40 US level bushels or 320 gallons ≡ 1.4095628066752 m³.
